{
  "Text": "[plang] Validate %step.ModuleType%, %stepResult.method%, %stepResult.data%\n    on error call HandleBuildStepFailure",
  "ModuleType": "PLang.Modules.ValidateModule",
  "GenericFunctionType": "PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+GenericFunction",
  "Function": {
    "Reasoning": "The user wants to validate that the variables %step.ModuleType%, %stepResult.method%, and %stepResult.data% are not empty. The appropriate function to use is IsNotEmpty, which checks if variables are empty and can generate an error message if validation fails. The error handling is specified separately and can be ignored in this step.",
    "Name": "IsNotEmpty",
    "Parameters": [
      {
        "Type": "System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Runtime.ObjectValue]",
        "Name": "variables",
        "Value": [
          "%step.ModuleType%",
          "%stepResult.method%",
          "%stepResult.data%"
        ]
      },
      {
        "Type": "PLang.Services.OutputStream.Messages.ErrorMessage",
        "Name": "errorMessage",
        "Value": {
          "Content": "One or more required variables are empty: %step.ModuleType%, %stepResult.method%, %stepResult.data%",
          "Key": "ValidationError",
          "Kind": "Error",
          "Level": "error",
          "StatusCode": 400,
          "Channel": "default",
          "Actor": "user"
        }
      }
    ],
    "ReturnValues": null
  },
  "Properties": {
    "Parameters": {
      "variables": {
        "Name": "variables",
        "FullTypeName": "System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Runtime.ObjectValue]"
      },
      "errorMessage": {
        "Name": "errorMessage",
        "FullTypeName": "PLang.Services.OutputStream.Messages.ErrorMessage"
      }
    },
    "ReturnValues": {}
  },
  "BuilderVersion": "0.1.18.1",
  "Hash": null,
  "SignedMessage": null,
  "LlmRequest": [
    {
      "temperature": 0.0,
      "top_p": 0.0,
      "frequencyPenalty": 0.0,
      "presencePenalty": 0.0,
      "maxLength": 4000,
      "llmResponseType": "json",
      "scheme": "{\"Reasoning\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Parameters\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter] = null, \"ReturnValues\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue] = null}\n\nAdditional information about objects:\nPLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Value\" : System.Object}\nPLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"VariableName\" : System.String}",
      "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
      "promptMessage": [
        {
          "role": "system",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "User is writing code in plang programming language.\r\n\r\nYour job is: \r\n1. Parse and understand user intent\r\n2. Map the intent to one of C# function provided to you\r\n3. Return a valid JSON\r\n\r\n## Rules\r\n%variable% in plang is defined with starting and ending percentage sign (%)\r\n%variable% MUST be wrapped in quotes(\") in json response, e.g. { \"name\":\"%name%\" }\r\nleave %variable% as is and do not change text to a variable\r\nnull is used to represent no value, e.g. { \"name\": null }\r\nVariables MUST not be changed, they can include dot(.) and parentheses()\r\nKeep \\n, \\r, \\t that are submitted to you for string variables\r\nParameters that is type System.String MUST be without escaping quotes. See <Example>\r\nError handling is process by another step, if you see 'on error...' you can ignore it\r\nIf there is some api key, settings, config replace it with %Settings.NameOfApiKey% \r\n- NameOfApiKey should named in relation to what is happening if change is needed\r\nDictionary<T1, T2> value is {key: value, ... } => a dictionary parameter defined as %variable% without key should have the same key and value as %variable%, e.g. %userId% => { key: \"userId\", value:\"%userId%\"}\r\nVariable with ToString with date/time formatting, assume it is System.DateTime, e.g. %updated.ToString(\"yyyy-MM-dd\")% then type of %updated% is System.DateTime \r\nList, ReadOnlyList are array of the object => e.g. user defines single property for List, return it as array\r\nWhen you see t%variable% or t\"this is text\", set the Type to Plang.TString. This is for translation\r\n<Example>\r\nget url \"http://example.org\" => Value: \"http://example.org\"\r\nwrite out 'Hello world' => Value: \"Hello world\"\r\n<Example>\r\n\r\n## JSON scheme information\r\nReasoning: A brief description of the reasoning behind the selection of the function and parameters based on the user's intent. This property provides context for why a particular function was chosen and how it aligns with the user intent.\r\nName: Name of the function to use from list of functions, if no function matches set as \"N/A\"\r\nParameters: List of parameters that are needed according to the user intent.\r\n- Type: the object type in c#\r\n- Name: name of the variable\r\n- Value: \"%variable%\", hardcode string that should be used, null, or json array/object\r\nReturnValue rules\r\n- Only if the function returns a value AND if user defines %variable% to write into, e.g. ' write into %data%' or 'into %result%', or simliar intent to write return value into variable\r\n- If no %variable% is defined then set as null."
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You MUST respond in JSON, scheme:\r\n {\"Reasoning\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Parameters\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter] = null, \"ReturnValues\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue] = null}  Additional information about objects: PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Value\" : System.Object} PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"VariableName\" : System.String}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "## Canonical User Intent (already disambiguated by LLM)\r\nThe user wants to validate the values of the variables %step.ModuleType%, %stepResult.method%, and %stepResult.data%, and if the validation fails, they want to call an error handling goal named HandleBuildStepFailure.\n## functions available starts ##\r\n{\"Description\":\"DO NOT USE for if statements. Validates a variable, make sure it's not empty, follows a pattern, is a number, etc. \",\"ExampleInformation\":\"Examples with methods first define an example plang code and then(=>) how it is mapped to parameters\",\"Methods\":[{\"Description\":\"Check each %variable% if it is empty. Create error message fitting the intent of the validation. channel=error|warning|info|debug|trace. channel is null unless sepecifically defined by user e.g. channel:error\",\"MethodName\":\"IsNotEmpty\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Runtime.ObjectValue]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Services.OutputStream.Messages.ErrorMessage\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"Description\":\"[Depricated] Check each %variable% if it is empty. Create error message fitting the intent of the validation. Extract all %variables% from this statement as a JSON array of strings, ensuring it is not wrapped as a single string. channel=error|warning|info|debug|trace. channel is null unless sepecifically defined by user e.g. channel:error\",\"MethodName\":\"IsNotEmpty\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Runtime.ObjectValue]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"statusCode\",\"DefaultValue\":400,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"compairer:==|<|>|<=|>=|!=\",\"MethodName\":\"IsLength\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"variableName\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"length\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"compairer\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"statusCode\",\"DefaultValue\":400,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Checks if variable contains a regex pattern. Create error message fitting the intent of the validation\",\"MethodName\":\"HasPattern\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String[]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"pattern\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"statusCode\",\"DefaultValue\":400,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Checks if variable is a valid 2 letter country code\",\"MethodName\":\"IsValid2LetterCountryCode\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String[]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"pattern\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"statusCode\",\"DefaultValue\":400,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"ValidateItemIsInList\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Object[]\",\"Name\":\"itemsToCheckInList\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.IList\",\"Name\":\"list\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"DefaultValue\":\"item is not in list\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"caseSensitive\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"List<Object>\"}},{\"Description\":\"Validates if signed contract is valid. Uses properties on the contract from signatureProperties as signatures to validate against. propertiesToMatch specifies properties that should be used on the validation, when null all poperties are used except signatureProperties\",\"MethodName\":\"ValidateSignedContract\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"contract\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"signatureProperties\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"propertiesToMatch\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"ValidateFileExtension\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"allowedExtensions\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"fileName\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"Description\":\"Validates that a value can be converted to a specified type. Supported types: long/int64, int/int32, short/int16, byte, double, float/single, decimal, bool/boolean, guid, datetime, string\",\"MethodName\":\"ValidateType\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ValidateModule.Program+TypeValidation\",\"Name\":\"validation\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"Examples\":[\"validate %id% is long => TypeValidation.Value=%id%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"long\\\"\",\"validate %price% is decimal => TypeValidation.Value=%price%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"decimal\\\"\",\"validate %price% is decimal with culture \\\"de-DE\\\" => TypeValidation.Value=%price%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"decimal\\\", TypeValidation.Culture=\\\"de-DE\\\"\",\"validate %count% is int => TypeValidation.Value=%count%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"int\\\"\",\"validate %isActive% is bool => TypeValidation.Value=%isActive%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"bool\\\"\",\"validate %userId% is guid => TypeValidation.Value=%userId%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"guid\\\"\",\"validate %startDate% is datetime => TypeValidation.Value=%startDate%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"datetime\\\"\",\"validate %startDate% is datetime format \\\"yyyy-MM-dd\\\" => TypeValidation.Value=%startDate%, TypeValidation.TypeName=\\\"datetime\\\", TypeValidation.Format=\\\"yyyy-MM-dd\\\"\"]}],\"SupportingObjects\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Runtime.ObjectValue]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"IsSystemVariable\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"Value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Type\",\"Name\":\"Type\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"Initiated\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.Properties\",\"Name\":\"Properties\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.DateTime\",\"Name\":\"Created\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.DateTime\",\"Name\":\"Updated\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Path\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Utils.StepHelper+CallbackInfo\",\"Name\":\"CallbackInfo\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"GoalName\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"GoalHash\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"StepIndex\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Answer\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.HashedData\",\"Name\":\"Data\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Type\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Format\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Hash\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.SignedMessage\",\"Name\":\"Signature\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Type\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Nonce\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.DateTimeOffset\",\"Name\":\"Created\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.DateTimeOffset\",\"Name\":\"Expires\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Name\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.HashedData\",\"Name\":\"Data\",\"Description\":\"(see PLang.Models.HashedData type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"Contracts\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"Headers\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.SignedMessage\",\"Name\":\"Parent\",\"TypeProperties\":[],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Identity\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Signature\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Utils.StepHelper+Callback\",\"Name\":\"Callback\",\"Description\":\"Content can be a filename or a text that will be written to stream. \\r\\nTarget defines where in the UI to write the content, this can be null and will be controlled by external system\\r\\nActions are actions executed on the content, built in actions are: 'replace, replaceSelf, append, prepend, appendOrReplace, prependOrReplace, scrollToTop, scrollIntoView, focus, highlight, show, hide, notify, alert, vibrate, navigate, replaceState, reload, open, close'. \\r\\nA user can define multiple actions, user:`render 'product.html' to #main, replace the content, navigate and scroll into view => Actions:[\\\"replace\\\", \\\"navigate\\\", \\\"scrollIntoView\\\"]\\r\\nLevel: trace|debug|info(default)|warning|error|critical. info is default. when user defines a level without a channel, assume channel=log\\r\\nChannel: default|log|audit|security|metric or custom defined by user\\r\\nActor: user|system => user is the default actor when Channel=default, for other channels use system as actor unless defined by user.\\r\\n\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Path\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"CallbackData\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Utils.StepHelper+CallbackInfo\",\"Name\":\"CallbackInfo\",\"Description\":\"(see PLang.Utils.StepHelper+CallbackInfo type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.SignedMessage\",\"Name\":\"Signature\",\"Description\":\"(see PLang.Models.SignedMessage type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Hash\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"PreviousHash\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Services.OutputStream.Messages.ErrorMessage\",\"Name\":\"errorMessage\",\"Description\":\"Content can be a filename or a text that will be written to stream. \\r\\nTarget defines where in the UI to write the content, this can be null and will be controlled by external system\\r\\nActions are actions executed on the content, built in actions are: 'replace, replaceSelf, append, prepend, appendOrReplace, prependOrReplace, scrollToTop, scrollIntoView, focus, highlight, show, hide, notify, alert, vibrate, navigate, replaceState, reload, open, close'. \\r\\nA user can define multiple actions, user:`render 'product.html' to #main, replace the content, navigate and scroll into view => Actions:[\\\"replace\\\", \\\"navigate\\\", \\\"scrollIntoView\\\"]\\r\\nLevel: trace|debug|info(default)|warning|error|critical. info is default. when user defines a level without a channel, assume channel=log\\r\\nChannel: default|log|audit|security|metric or custom defined by user\\r\\nActor: user|system => user is the default actor when Channel=default, for other channels use system as actor unless defined by user.\\r\\n\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Content\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"FixSuggestion\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"HelpfullLinks\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Utils.StepHelper+Callback\",\"Name\":\"Callback\",\"Description\":\"(see PLang.Utils.StepHelper+Callback type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Services.OutputStream.Messages.MessageKind\",\"Name\":\"Kind\",\"AvailableValues\":\"Text|Render|Error|Execute|Ask|Stream\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Level\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"StatusCode\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Target\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyList`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"Actions\",\"Description\":\"Content can be a filename or a text that will be written to stream. \\r\\nTarget defines where in the UI to write the content, this can be null and will be controlled by external system\\r\\nActions are actions executed on the content, built in actions are: 'replace, replaceSelf, append, prepend, appendOrReplace, prependOrReplace, scrollToTop, scrollIntoView, focus, highlight, show, hide, notify, alert, vibrate, navigate, replaceState, reload, open, close'. \\r\\nA user can define multiple actions, user:`render 'product.html' to #main, replace the content, navigate and scroll into view => Actions:[\\\"replace\\\", \\\"navigate\\\", \\\"scrollIntoView\\\"]\\r\\nLevel: trace|debug|info(default)|warning|error|critical. info is default. when user defines a level without a channel, assume channel=log\\r\\nChannel: default|log|audit|security|metric or custom defined by user\\r\\nActor: user|system => user is the default actor when Channel=default, for other channels use system as actor unless defined by user.\\r\\n\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Channel\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Actor\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyDictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"Properties\",\"Description\":\"Content can be a filename or a text that will be written to stream. \\r\\nTarget defines where in the UI to write the content, this can be null and will be controlled by external system\\r\\nActions are actions executed on the content, built in actions are: 'replace, replaceSelf, append, prepend, appendOrReplace, prependOrReplace, scrollToTop, scrollIntoView, focus, highlight, show, hide, notify, alert, vibrate, navigate, replaceState, reload, open, close'. \\r\\nA user can define multiple actions, user:`render 'product.html' to #main, replace the content, navigate and scroll into view => Actions:[\\\"replace\\\", \\\"navigate\\\", \\\"scrollIntoView\\\"]\\r\\nLevel: trace|debug|info(default)|warning|error|critical. info is default. when user defines a level without a channel, assume channel=log\\r\\nChannel: default|log|audit|security|metric or custom defined by user\\r\\nActor: user|system => user is the default actor when Channel=default, for other channels use system as actor unless defined by user.\\r\\n\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.IList\",\"Name\":\"list\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"Item\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ThrowErrorModule.ErrorInfo\",\"Name\":\"Error\",\"Description\":\"Error information if validation fails\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Message\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Type\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"StatusCode\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Key\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ValidateModule.Program+TypeValidation\",\"Name\":\"validation\",\"Description\":\"Configuration for type validation\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"Value\",\"Description\":\"The value to validate\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"TypeName\",\"Description\":\"Type to validate against. Supported: long, int64, int, int32, short, int16, byte, double, float, single, decimal, bool, boolean, guid, datetime, string\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Format\",\"Description\":\"Format string for datetime validation, e.g. 'yyyy-MM-dd', 'dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss'\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Culture\",\"Description\":\"Culture for number/date parsing, e.g. 'en-US', 'de-DE', 'is-IS'. Defaults to InvariantCulture\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ThrowErrorModule.ErrorInfo\",\"Name\":\"Error\",\"Description\":\"(see PLang.Modules.ThrowErrorModule.ErrorInfo type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"IsRequired\":false}]}\r\n## functions available ends ##\r\n## defined variables ##\r\nstep.ModuleType (type:object), stepResult.method (type:object), stepResult.data (type:object), \r\n## defined variables ##"
            }
